item.description: We see plenty of configuration languages, but surprisingly one has not become the one true language that is used everywhere. Why is that? One would think writing out data structures by hand would not be that hard. Why not configure everything in JSON and call it a day? If JSON does not provide enough abstraction to do the job, why not pick a general programming language like Python? Not for a lack of effort, the industry has failed to standardize on a solution that we are satisfied with and move on.
